    "text": "Erdős Problem #100: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $A$ be a set of $n$ points in $\\mathbb{R}^2$ such that all pairwise distances are at least $1$ and if two distinct distances differ then they differ by at least $1$. Is the diameter of $A$ $\\gg n$? Current best: The bounds on the distinct distance problem [89] proved by Guth and Katz \\cite{GuKa15} imply a lower bound of $\\gg n/\\log n$. Prize: no. Tags: distances, geometry.",
